service: This is the Amazon Lookout for Metrics API Reference. For an introduction to the service with tutorials for getting started, visit Amazon Lookout for Metrics Developer Guide.

operations.BackTestAnomalyDetector: Runs a backtest for anomaly detection for the specified resource.
operations.CreateAlert: Creates an alert for an anomaly detector.
operations.DeleteAnomalyDetector: Deletes a detector. Deleting an anomaly detector will delete all of its corresponding resources including any configured datasets and alerts.
operations.DescribeAlert:
Describes an alert.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.DescribeAnomalyDetectionExecutions: Returns information about the status of the specified anomaly detection jobs.
operations.DescribeAnomalyDetector:
Describes a detector.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.DescribeMetricSet:
Describes a dataset.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.GetAnomalyGroup: Returns details about a group of anomalous metrics.
operations.GetSampleData: Returns a selection of sample records from an Amazon S3 datasource.
operations.ListAlerts:
Lists the alerts attached to a detector.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.ListAnomalyDetectors:
Lists the detectors in the current AWS Region.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.ListAnomalyGroupRelatedMetrics: Returns a list of measures that are potential causes or effects of an anomaly group.
operations.ListAnomalyGroupTimeSeries: Gets a list of anomalous metrics for a measure in an anomaly group.
operations.ListMetricSets:
Lists the datasets in the current AWS Region.

Amazon Lookout for Metrics API actions are eventually consistent. If you do a read operation on a resource immediately after creating or modifying it, use retries to allow time for the write operation to complete.
operations.ListTagsForResource: Gets a list of tags for a detector, dataset, or alert.
operations.TagResource: Adds tags to a detector, dataset, or alert.
operations.UntagResource: Removes tags from a detector, dataset, or alert.
operations.UpdateAnomalyDetector: Updates a detector. After activation, you can only change a detector's ingestion delay and description.
